Temiloluwa O’Peters The management of CFS Group Plc, a subsidiary of Cititrust Holdings Plc, has announced a change of name of three of its subsidiaries after getting approval from its board and shareholders. A statement issued by the Group on Wednesday noted that the decision was aimed at rebranding the affected companies to reflect their renewed focus on service delivery. The Country Chief Executive, Mr Ikechukwu Peter, stated that the change of name of the strategic business units became necessary to enhance brand visibility and synergy. According to the statement, the affected subsidiaries are Core Capital Limited, which is now Cititrust Financial Services Limited; First Option Microfinance Bank Limited, which is now Cititrust Microfinance Bank Limited; and Bermuda Forex BDC Limited, which has become Cititrust BDC Limited. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 